omplete proof of its coherent analogue: the Waldspurger formula, which relates the periods of integrals and the special values of L-series by means of Weil representations. The Gross-Zagier formula is then reformulated in terms of incoherent Weil representations and Kudla's generating series. Using Arakelov theory and the modularity of Kudla's generating series, the proof of the Gross-Zagier formula is reduced to local formulas. The Gross-Zagier Formula on Shimura Curves will be of great use to students wishing to enter this area and to those already working in it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aArithmetical algebraic geometry. 0aAutomorphic forms. 0aQuaternions. 0aShimura varieties. 7aMATHEMATICS / Number Theory.2bisacsh  aArakelov theory.  aBenedict Gross.  aDon Zagier.  aEichlerГhimura theory.  aEisenstein series.  aGrossКagier formula.  aHeegner point.  aHodge bundle.  aHodge index theorem.  aL-series.  aMordellЗeil group.  aNeronДate height.  aRankinГelberg L-function.  aSchwartz function.  aShimizu lifting.  aShimura curve.  aShimura curves.  aSiegelЗeil formula.  aWaldspurger formula.  aWeil representation.  aabelian varieties.  aanalytic kernel function.  aanalytic kernel.  adegenerate Schwartz function.  adiscrete series.  agenerating series.  ageometric kernel.  aheight series.  aholomorphic kernel function.  aholomorphic projection.  aincoherent Eisenstein series.  aincoherent automorphic representation.  aincoherent quaternion algebra.  akernel function.  akernel identity.  alocal height.  amodular curve.  amodularity.  amultiplicity function.  anon-archimedean local field.  anon-degenerate quadratic space.  aordinary component.  aorthogonal space.  aprojector.  apull-back formula.  aramified quadratic exten